Join us today, March 23, from 6 to 8 PM, for the opening of Alicia Framis' first exhibition KÖNIG GALERIE. For LEAVE HERE YOUR FEARS, Framis has constructed a mirrored steel sculpture that will occupy the center point of the Chapel at St. Agnes in Berlin.

This durational, interactive show involves two distinct moments, both anchored to the reflective object at its core. The first involves Framis’ invitation to viewers to write down their greatest fears and troubling thoughts and deposit them into a small opening on the sculpture’s mirrored surface. Once collected, the second moment involves Framis’ act of removing the anonymous missives and transferring them to stretched sections of canvas that will then cover the chapel walls, creating an installation that takes shape over the course of the exhibition’s run.

